"Brigham Young University (often referred to as BYU, or sometimes just the Y) is a private university located in Provo, Utah, United States. It is owned and operated by The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS Church), and is the largest religious university and third-largest private university in the U.S. Approximately 98% of the university's 34,000 students are members of the LDS Church, and one-third of its American students come from within the state of Utah."@en
